  "prompt": "How do I uninstall Modified apk by Lucky Patcher (I can only deactivate it)?",
  "response": "If you have used Lucky Patcher to modify an APK and now want to uninstall that modified version but can only deactivate it, here\u2019s a step-by-step guide on how to proceed:\n\n### Uninstalling Modified APK\n\n1. **Deactivate** the Modified APK:\n   - Open Lucky Patcher.\n   - Find the modified app you want to uninstall in the list.\n   - Tap on the app, then choose **'Deactivate'** if that option is available. This will restore the app to its original state.\n\n2. **Uninstall the App:**\n   - Go to your device's **Settings**.\n   - Navigate to **Apps** or **Applications** (this may vary depending on your device).\n   - Scroll through the list and find the modified app.\n   - Tap on the app, then select **Uninstall**.\n   - Confirm the uninstallation.\n\n3. **Reinstall the Original App (if needed):**\n   - If you want to restore the original version of the app, you can do so by going to the Google Play Store or obtaining the original APK from a trusted source.\n\n### Additional Steps (if you encounter issues):\n\n- **Clear Cache and Data**:\n   - Before uninstalling, you may want to clear the cache and data of the app through the app settings in your device.\n\n- **Check for Device Administrator**:\n   - If the app is set as a device administrator, you might need to remove it from the device administrators list in Settings > Security > Device Administrators.\n\n- **Use Third-Party App Management Tools**:\n   - If you still can't uninstall the app, consider using third-party app management tools available on the Play Store to help uninstall stubborn apps.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to successfully uninstall the modified APK from your device.",
